Under 980 nm laser excitation, the emission spectra of GZBL-Er and CZBL-Er powders with sundry pumping powers are depicted in Fig. 2(a,b), and four emission bands centered at 408, 522, 544 and 653 nm are attributed to f-f transitions 2H9/2 → 4I15/2, 2H11/2 → 4I15/2, 4S3/2 → 4I15/2 and 4F9/2 → 4I15/2, respectively. As the excitation power increases, the intensity of each peak increases exponentially, and the upconversion emission intensity Ilumin is proportional to the nth power of the 980 nm excitation intensity Iexcit, which can be simply expressed as Ilumin∝Iexcitn\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
